<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-21T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-21T09:00:00-05:00" n="868" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d868">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5561/72: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-21T17:00:00+03:00">November 21, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 22—10:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1959. Department’s 1195, November 7, 11 a.m.<note n="61" xml:id="d868fn61">Not printed.</note> In a note dated November 20
                            and received today the Foreign Office states in substance that the
                            Soviet Government will permit an Assistant Naval Attaché of the Embassy
                            to remain in Archangel. It adds however that in consideration of the
                            military situation the authorities deem it inexpedient to allow an
                            Assistant Naval Attaché to be stationed at one of the Black Sea ports at
                            present and that decision on this matter must therefore be
                            postponed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>